\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Did the teachers at your first school emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Religion. And arithmetic. Those two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What about things like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I can't remember that, of course - my - father used to teach us manners, mother and father you see. And we wasn't taught it the easy way, you should do this, you should do that. We sat at the table, and if you picked a knife or fork u
p wrong my father would just tap you with the - the - with the knife. You had to remember next time. So we was brought up very strict. Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 He was strict with a lot of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 At school did the teachers emphasise things like tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Yes. Yes, well we were always tidy, it was a nice school and people were - you know - neatly dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes. Oh very punctual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What would have happened if you were late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I don't think I was ever late. 
Oh - you'd probably have to stay behind five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, they didn't teach you anything there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
At your first school if you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 They'd cane your hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 The girls the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You were only girls weren't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, we were only girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What sort of things would you have your hands canned for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Being cheeky. Being naughty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I can't remember much else, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh father was very good, at night - he would have us round the table - and - teach us sums, mental arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did they meet the teachers ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, the majority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did the teachers single out some children for
 different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well it all depends whether you was clever or not. You see I was fortunate, I was clever. And - I can remember once, we had a very nice - scripture teacher. And - when the inspectors used to come they used to say
 to me, you sit down, we know you know. So I never got a chance. Oh now they had this scripture lesson and - oh I kept putting me hand up for everything that was said, and probably some things I didn't know but I put me hand up for it, and - she gave four
 people a threepenny bit. Well I was very disappointed, I didn't get one. But when - prize giving came I got first prize. For arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What about the children who weren't so clever as you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh they just - no, they just normal - just went - you
 know, normally on, they wasn't pushed forward in anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I can't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How long did you stay at your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well was there all the time 'til I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Was there anything different to tell me about when you were older, you stayed right through to fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 'Til I was fourteen you see. Then I won a scholarship to go to the
 high school. But - my father was in business, and - he put the business before my education. So - I had to go into his business. For eleven months you see, and then - anyway - after - I had to be in my father's business and - the woman, she was quite rou
g
h and she kept the next shop to us. And - one day she came to me and she said, do you know where babies come from? I says, no, I don't. So she said, oh, she said, I'll stop and tell you, so - luckily, my mother came in the shop. So I said, Mrs Mills wants
 
to know if I know where babies come from. She said, oh does she. Like that. So what mother said to her I don't know. But the next thing my father said, well it's time you started work. And he took me straight out the shop and put me to the place where I w
as you see then. Yes, I can always remember that, 'cos I never knew where babies - and I was fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
A lady I saw yesterday didn't know anything about this until she was engaged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Had you been told about menstruation or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
No, nothing, it just - no, you had to find that out yourself. No, you never was explained anything in those days. The - your parents wouldn't speak to you about anything like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your mother tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes, afterwards. Afterwards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 She told you the proper way did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
No. Oh no, I didn't know. I know the first boy I went with - he said, may I kiss you, so - I said, yes, must there. And he kissed me on my cheek, and I thought if he kissed me on the lips I'd have a baby. 
You see, you didn't know. Know what - none of us knew then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 It must have been terribly frightening for people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well it was. I used to say to myself, I wouldn't let any man touch me, he had to keep away from me you know. I was frightened to death
. No, no one knew anything. And this girl used to say - cheeky things one to another - we - would walk away. Wouldn't listen to it. Thought it was terrible. Oh no, didn't know anything. And girls didn't know anything 'til they was married, you see, you we
re just thrown in head first. Oh yes, they were. They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And the boys presumably told each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Probably they did, I don't know, but we was never allowed to speak about anything in the house. In fact father wouldn't allow you, he said, you h
ave to sit there and - be listened to, you see, listen to us and - we weren't allowed to speak or - even when I went to work and came home with troubles, father would shut it up immediately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What sort of troubles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well, I don't know, perhaps thi
ngs went wrong, little bits of things went wrong at work you see and I'd come home and say, oh well, so and so, you know to mother, and cry to mother. Father wouldn't allow you if he was there. We used to get mother on the side you see and talk to her and
 she'd put it right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes I do. Oh I could have gone on a long way. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - yes, because you - I got on well you see, I studied and I
 - you see, I am a person that if - if you're going to get somewhere I'll get there. And I'll struggle but I'll get there, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You were fourteen when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I was fourteen, but I started work when I was fourteen and ten months. Ne
arly fifteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Could you tell me about how you helped with the family business when you were younger, because it didn't come off very clear on the tape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh didn't it? Well - we had a fruit business at one - one time there was fruit, the other si
de was fish. And - I was about six years of age and I used to have to sit and wait for the - vegetables and everything coming from the market so as nobody'd take them you see. And I can remember one sergeant, I'll never forget it, he came from the market 
a
nd he'd got a big codfish, a big one. And he came to me and said, missie, can I have some paper? I said, no. I said, my dad bought this paper, you go and get your paper where you got your fish. And instead of calling me Carlile they used to call me - Kali
.
 Kali, you know, they you see I was little and - all the - yes, the police used to come, they used to - go in the market see and they'd give 'em to keep 'em - a big fish, I can always remember this sergeant coming with this big codfish. And he said, will 
you give me a piece of paper missie? I said, no, I won't. I said, my dad's bought that, I said, you go and get your fish - get your paper where you got your fish from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So you had to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes, help. Yes. About six years of age. I wouldn't serv
e, but I would be helping seeing nobody took the things early morning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What sort of hours were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well, I don't know about then, I wouldn't be there many hours when I was six, but later on I should be only eight, nine, somewhere 
round those ages, we used to work in the morning - about seven in the morning 'til twelve at night. Twelve o'clock at night, yes. When people turned out the pubs about eleven - you'd do more business then than during the day. Oh yes, a lot of business. Es
pecially at Christmas time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So when you left school what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I went in there, I was there about ten months with my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What were you doing at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh well I'd be serving. I was serving, yes, serving in the shop then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What hours did you work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well we used to work then - quite late. And - and then afterwards - the - the Government changed the hours 'til nine o'clock at night. Then we used to work 'til nine at night you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When was that do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I - I should imagine that - during the first world war I should think. As early as that, I know I was delighted when we finished at nine. 'Cos - I never went out on a Saturday night 'til I was thirty-five, I was not allowed - I did not
, my dad - no, I didn't, I had to stop there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you were working for your father? Were you paid then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well, no, he didn't actually pay us but he always - well we used to clean his shoes for a ha'penny, remember that when we was kids, and - he
'd make us all clean - well all had to clean 'em, and he said, who - who - when I can see my face in the shoes, he said, then I'll know they're all right. So each one of cleaned them in turn, all the whole time you see, and so to get a ha'penny each, but 
we all had to - do those shoes for him you see. The same pair of shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you working at the business were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - mother gave me half a crown every week which - put it in the bank and every week I put half a crown in the bank you see, and we used to say that was my - money. And then he bought all our clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 But when you left school what happened? Was it different then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh no, he always bought our clothes, and - looked after the tables well, you see. And - at Easter time h
e always bought new shoes, Whitsuntide always clothes, whether we needed them or not, we always - looked after us well you know. Although he was a very strict man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So your life didn't really suddenly change when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, no, not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What about when you got your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 After you'd had the discussion with the lady next door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Yes, well - I started as an errand girl. And - we used to - have to - well we used to go and fetch the girls the
 teas, we used to take - cups on a big tray, and be a farthingsworth of milk, ha'penny worth of - ha'penny worth of cucumber salmon in another cup, this is what the girls used to have for their tea. Ha'pennyworth, yes, got a piece of salmon, and it was th
e
 best salmon, and perhaps one or two little bits of cucumber and - we used to go down - to man - old man named Gray and in the cream jug we used to get cream for the boss. He used to tell us to serve ourselves, we used to serve ourselves, but cream we use
d
 to drink and then serve again. We did, it was awful then. And - well that's what we did for the teatime, then we took them back, you see, they used to have a good tea for about threefarthings, everyday, a farthings worth of milk and - and that, and we us
e
d to have to carry 'em down a - we used to have a good way, about ten minutes to walk, and we used to have to carry a big tray like this full of cups, all the girls cups. Well eventually that was all - the - done away with and then - then we had a canteen
 
and then they allowed them to go down to the canteen and we used to have to take - the tea up in - in teapots you see. And they used to bring their own milk and - and that and we used to bring the teaport. Well then one girl, she fell down so that was don
e
 away with, hurt herself you see with a teapot, scalding teapot you see so that was done away with. And then - we used to have to take all the parcels out, and there was another girl, I was always tall, there was another girl next to me, she was little, s
o
 we - I used to help her to pile all the - parcels in a big hampers and I used to help her push it, I used to walk at the side see if anybody come in. She used to push the hamper. Well I was too proud, I didn't want folks to see me pushing the hamper. But
 if I saw anybody about I used to put me hand on it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What else did you do as an errand girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - we used to do - a little bits of things inside - oh in the morning - we had to have - seven o'clock in the morning 'til eight o'clock to sweep. Y
es. Seven to eight to sweep. We got a shilling a week for that. And then - and one morning I got there at six and policeman come, he says, what's the matter, missie, what are you doing here? I said, well to open. He said, what time have you got to be here
?
 I said, seven. He said, it's only six. I got there at six, I - so anyway, then we used to do that and then - we worked then from nine 'til whatever time the work was out, seven o'clock, sometimes eight o'clock at night you see. We got five shillings a we
ek for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So that was a shilling extra and the five shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And the five shillings a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, we didn't work Saturday, just five days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 We did not, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you started did you think that was a fair wage or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I didn't know you see. In fact I - I didn't want to go and work where I did go and work, but of course my parents made me and there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 They found the job for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes. My mother got me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you give any of the money you earned to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh I gave it to her all. Used to give us a threepennorth back. And I used to have to buy me own ribbons for me hair, 'cos we had - four inch ribbons down like that for your hair with a bow at the back you see. So I had to buy my ribbons out of that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well the first one - not too cleve
r. He was a - a little - little crippled man, and he'd got - he had got some lovely daughters. But - but every Tuesday we used to have to go to his place in the park, bring back his hot dinner and hot water - and rush back and then come home for your dinn
er, never give you any time, we had to come home for dinner and get back to work then by two o'clock just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How long did it take you to get to the park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
It would take me - we'd got to go right down - you know - Sneinton market hall, we went down -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 It would take you about quarter of an hour wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 It would. It would. I had to race home like mad, yes, to get back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And he never gave you anything extra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, he did not. And then when they had a rise - all the people 
had a rise and - oh that'd be late on in life though, all the people had a rise and all the - the women was grumbling, of course - we were young, and we'd got a rise. So I worked it all out. So one day I went to him, I said, Mr Baldock - that's me - Mr. B
a
ldock. He said, yes, what can I do for you? I said, you can work my money out please on this paper. He worked it out, I said, thank you very much. He gave me a penny, right, so I go back to the department and said, do you know how much we've got increase 
in wage? Said, no. I said, one penny. That's all they'd given us. One penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 A week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes, a week. Oh yes. One penny. Only a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
So - anyway, I said, look, you keep your penny Mr Baldock, keep your penny and giv
e me my proper wage. And I can remember when we earnt five shillings a week and a shilling for sweeping. And then one day - the under-manager, he was a charming man, he said to me, I want to put you on your own time. I said, oh Mr Parkes, I'll never earn 
t
he money, I'll never - he said, you will. I said, I won't really. He said, look, if you don't earn double five shillings I'll give it to you. I said, will you really, are you sure? He says, yes. So I go on me own time and earn twelve and six first week in
stead of five bob you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I should be - I was only - I should only be just turned fifteen 'cos I was only - I was too quick for being an errand girl, I was only errand girl about three months. Three months errand girl
 and then - then we went on from - see we had to go through all the stages of the lace trade. Well then - that was on a machine to join the ends of lace together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Can you tell me the proper name for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - we were joiner. Then we went as j
oiner. And used to have to - find the right and wrong of your work, go through every bit through your fingers like that, so there's no damage you see, and cut the damage out and join it. Then you got perhaps sevenpence for that, a hundred - hundred joins 
o
n your machine. Well then when that was finished we - you went on measuring - and - once my - measuring machine jumped, and - all the work was wrong. When we came home - we couldn't - we had to calculate our own tickets. Couldn't make it right no matter w
h
at we did. So just when we - they closed the firm down we - a girl and me, I told her I said, everything's wrong here, I don't know what's the matter, and it's the machine not me at fault. So we undid a card and it wasn't right, it should have been a hund
red and forty-four yards, well it was anyhow. So we told the man that was ship - shipping next morning to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, it was all created. So he said, look, don't worry, he said, it's all - they'd got it all in the cases for the ship. So the next morning anothe
r girl - two girls and me and the manager, the under - manager and the man in the packing room, all went, took it all out, and we took it and we measured every bit. We got it away for eleven o'clock, I don't know how we did it, but we managed and the tick
e
t came out right, you see, the clock had jumped. Well that was one excitement. Oh we had a lot of excitements. Well then after being a measurer like that there was a hand measurer. You see, everything done by hand. That was very tiny narrow baby laces. We
l
l then from that you went to be - a counter in. Now that means - the man gives the work out and when the - women outside bring it back you've got to count it in. And I can remember once a piece came back, and I didn't know there was - somebody had cut an 
e
dge in two. So that was two in two bits. Well they had the makers in, I said, well I know, I said, there's so many bits in there. She said there can't be. I said, well I know there is. But what I didn't know is, the woman had got some bad work, she'd cut 
i
t in two, you see. Anyway the man - he - he brought me a big box of chocolates, he said, I'll give you a box of chocolates if you find that. I said, well I have. That - anyway that - that was that, and we passed that. And then from hand measuring we went 
o
n to ginnying. Do you know what ginnying is? Putting lace on a card. See on the - well you have a machine with a handle too, and - you've got to - they've got two prong like that, a prong here and a prong there and a handle here and you just go like that 
and you put a card on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And you did it by hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
By hand. Yes. Hand ginnying that is. Of course today they can do it by machine but we couldn't those days, so this is antique. I went on there and then our department unfortunately went through, we 
didn't get the work see. We was the first slack department. Well when the department wound up, I was surprised - as they - oh, before then - yes, our department went through, that's right, our department went through, and I heard there was a job going in 
a
nother section. So I said to the girl next to me, I said, I've a good mind to go and ask for that job, I said, I don't like it in here. Oh they'd changed our room, I said, I don't like it in here. And in front of my ginny I'd put a big mirror up so as I c
o
uld see anybody coming at that back. Oh I did. And the first person I saw was Mr Paul Myers, the boss. I said, Mary lock that - Mary knock that mirror down, Mary knock the mirror down. We couldn't get it down. Anyway he tapped me on the shoulder and there
 
was I - I nearly went under the counter. So he said, Missie, I want you. So I got off and - and Mr - the boss who was afterwards, Mr Baker, he stood there, and he said, Mr Paul Myer said, Mr Baker wants a good lassie to work in his department. I said, tha
nk you sir, it's very kind of you. So he said, you know Missie, we want a girl with brains. I said, Mr Myer, everybody's born with brains but it's up to the person how they used them. I'd never spoken to him in me life before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh I should be about - be about twenty-six, twenty-eight, somewhere there. He says, I'll take you on three months. Well - then the three months I'd done so well - and he came downstairs to see me. And when I first went down there his counters, Mr Baker
's counters was full of work, right to the ceiling. And - I cleared it, and I got two girls to work for me. I made 'em work, didn't I used to make 'em work. I used to take some - 'course I was quick, I took some bars of chocolate, I said, now who does so 
m
any parcels going to get a bar of chocolate. And of course I were always - I could do three to their two, three to their one sometimes, so - we used to like work like mad, and so did I. Anyway he came down and he said - he came to congratulate me. He said
, do you like the work? I said, like it, I love it. It was exciting you see to get the work out. So - he gave me a rise, half a crown.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What were you called in the new department?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - I was just then in the stockroom you see. And then - one da
y - Mr Baker, he was manager, he met me on the stairs, he said, you know I'm going to have you upstairs. I said, what for? So he said, to do the books. I said, do you mean it? He said, yes. Oh, that's what I've wanted all my life, to do books. You see I w
a
s that way given. I said, oh yes, yes. So I went upstairs and then I came to be - the supervisor you see, over the whole department. And he said to me, in future - he had them all in, he said, this is Miss Carlile, and you're not to call her by her Christ
i
an name ever - anymore, this is Miss Carlile. You see, then, oh I thought heart's desire, and - it - he wasn't quite the boss just then. The - the other man - there's another man there, the boss, and he said to me, has he given you a rise? So I said, yes.
 
He said, how much? I said, a shilling. He said have you kept it? I said, no I haven't, I gave it him back. He give me a shilling rise to do a man's job. So I says, oh now, Mr Walker, you take that shilling back, I said, I don't need it, you see. So anyway
 
when Mr Baker came up, they - they soon started to give me extra money you see. And I tried to live on the money I'd already had and save that - for when I was older you see. And - oh I - done all sort of things to - I've made and sold things on purpose o
f getting money but - I never - they kept giving me a hundred pound now and again, the bosses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you save it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh yes, saved it, it all went to the bank. I know the first time - the first time that I was in the stock room, I was - I was really v
ery worried because at Christmas time came, and when we'd gone through all the stock I was three pound out, all the - now I didn't know at the time but we'd had thousands and thousands of poundsworth of stock - well when I balanced the books I was three p
o
und out you know, and I was crying. And the boss went after me. He said, what are you here for? I said, I haven't had that three pound, I didn't know how to balance the books. He said, come back, they want you at our office, congratulated me and - it was 
marvelous to me, and I thought it was terrible losing three pounds. Said, no, you can lose that in inches, in inches you see. And every Christmas he used to give me a nice bonus. I remember when we did well they used go give me extra bonus you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How long you were in the stockroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh I was in the stockroom I think - about two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Can you remember what you were paid then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Twenty-eight shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, I didn't, it was shocking, I mean t
he man used to get that before me, twenty-eight shillings, that's all he got a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I meant at the time did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
No. No, I thought it was bad. Yes, certainly. But - now, my father kept me there, I shouldn't have kept th
ere because - I did get a job to leave there, to go to the Valley to be their supervisor at the Valley. And - my father, if - if you go there you leave this house, you see, he kept us down you see, he kept me there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Why was that? Because you would have been bettering yourself wouldn't you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh absolutely, he couldn't see that, all he thought of was himself, 
\lquote cos at weekends I had to work in his shop. And I was never allowed out, I worked in his shop 'til I was thirty-five. I never went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 This is why he wanted you to have a five day week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 That's right, yes. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So you worked at his shop all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
All the time, yes. And then I took me books home, I worked with Mr Baker, he was the boss, at his house on Sundays. I never had much life. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I take it from what you said you thoroughly enjoyed the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh I did. I did. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And when you were earning more did you
 still give all the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh no. No. I - I paid her about fourteen shillings a week. Oh yes, I paid her - about fourteen shillings a week I think I paid her. Well I just can't remember when it changed but - I can remember when I got three pound a week I kept the house going.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well now I don't just remember, I can tell you what happened in Nottingham, the big Tattoo on the Forest, it was that year, that's all I can tell you. It was that year because I went, I was high up in heaven 'cos they gave me three pound a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What about holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh we didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you have any paid holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh they didn't - when I had a holiday - I - I think I was six months asking them for a fortnight
's holiday, and they wouldn't allow me to have it, and at the finish I said, you can keep your holiday, I don't want it. I was so good tempered in asking them for a holiday, and they wasn't paying me, I'd got to pay. No, we didn't have paid holidays.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No. Not 'til the last two years. Then we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So you stayed with the same firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, fifty-two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you still get called supervisor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh yes, oh that - no, no, I was like a manageress there. I was a manageress there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When were you changed from being called a supervisor to a manageress?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh I think about - well not long after I was a supervisor, not long after because I got - I took another woman in to be a supervisor you see and then I was over them all you see. Over the men as well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What would you have liked to have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - I wanted to be in charge, I mean that's in me blood, I - I can't help that, that's in me, lik
e me dad. You see. Well - I - I don't know, I would have liked to have gone to - Raleigh where I got the - you know. I - I was chosen out of about seventy-two people. Then the finish he wouldn't let me go, said I'd got to leave home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I should think I'd be about thirty, oh no, more than that, perhaps about - about thirty-four I should think, somewhere there, I can't just remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So you really did what you were told?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh I had to do. Had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What would have happened if you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I'd have - left home. He wouldn't have me back you see, he - he was a - what he said was law, you couldn't go against it. In fact it wasn't - 'til we was quite grown up that I went against him, and one Sunday morni
ng I sat knitting. The war must have been on, I sat knitting. And - mother says, oh please put it away, your father's getting up, your father's getting up. I said, well I'm not. I was just turning then, I wasn't going to let him do what he liked with me y
o
u see, so anyway when he got up he said, what do you think you're doing? I said, knitting. So he said, you can put that away. I said, look, they don't tell soldiers to put themselves away and soldiers fighting for them these are socks, it wasn't, it was m
y jumper. He never said another work, he went in the other room you see. No, he never said another word 'cos he thought it was socks for soldiers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You didn't serve an apprenticeship did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well this was like an apprenticeship, fourteen to eight
een. In fact - I think I've destroyed it now, I did have a certificate, you see, you had to know every detail about the lace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So all that was really training was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 All training that was, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you have to sign any papers for the training?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I did because I - I think I've destroyed it now, I had a certificate to say I had passed all grades. You see, and then I used to be - I used to - when I come to be manageress I used to buy - buy and - used to buy from the makers, they hadn'
t got any machines then and we had them later - later on, and - my boss, he was very very clever at mental arithmetic. And - he used to - if a man came in to buy some goods, and I used to, I - always with him you see. Eighty-two and a half per cent off. H
e knew instantly. So I went home to my dad and I said, he can do eighty-two and a half per cent, he doesn't think. So all right, we had it on the table, 'til one day we had a man come in at the office to buy some stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So you were saying you served the equivalent of an apprenticeship really?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were there any you could have belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I - I'm not a believer in trade unions anyhow. I think the trade unions are running the country. I wouldn't have done, no, I - I like to be a free agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you think employers and workers had the same interests or different?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I don't know. Interest in what? Anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were they aiming for the same sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes. Oh yes
. Oh yes, yes. The workers were good workers. And they'd go down, I'd say, I've got a boat to catch certain time, and always used to give a day - in case anything let us down you see, and they'd work for it. Absolutely keen, keen workers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, there were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 In what sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well some were jealous of the others and - you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I - I didn't feel it you see because I was always there, I was always there amongst the top you see. What I didn't know I - I soon got to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well it gave me better prospects. I should say yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You weren't in fact treated any differently at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh no. Oh no, no, no, everything - no, everything was just the same. Our father still bought our clothes and still did this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Did anything special happen in those days when you were twenty-one? Were you thought of as grown up or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh no, not like that, well you - you was given a party. But I can remember - I was very disappointed with my tw
enty-first birthday. Very disappointed. My father bought me a - a gold watch, a gold bangle, but instead of just giving me for my twenty-first a gold bangle he buys my sister one. Well it didn't interest me any more, I said he could take it back, I didn't
 want it. It was my birthday, not my sister's. She was only eighteen. I was twenty-one, he bought us both one you see. That was all, I didn't have a party or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 From what you say you worked terrific long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Can you tell me anything about your life at home after you left school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well there wasn't much at home at all, only we just go out to play that was all. Oh and on a Sunday - oh at the weekend, and in the evening, we had a piano and my brother used to play the pi
ano and we used to sing and - Saturday and Sunday nights we had - party gatherings you know, we was allowed to take our friends home, we had sing-songs at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You were allowed to take your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes. You wasn't allowed to take boys home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 But you worked Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, I worked Saturdays for my father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So did you have any free time on a Saturday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No we didn't. Barring Saturday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Sunday did you go to church or chapel still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - yes, w
e went to church and then I used to have to go to the - if I went in the morning I went to the bosses house in the afternoon, if I went in the evening I went to the bosses house in the morning. You see, we didn't have all the books we have today. Your bra
in was your books. You only had one book. Your brain was your books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You remembered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
You had to remember. Everything. You could remember everything, everything that went off. And then - you had a - one book for the main - answer. But everything e
lse was carried in your head. It was. Yes. But when I left there they got twenty books, because I - 1928 I had - fever. Partyphoid, and - oh all the heads come here, all the heads come here, not here but me mother's home you see, and I can remember Mr Ley
ton stood outside and he said - I won't come in, but everything she wants she can have. So my dad said, and anything she wants I can pay for, he was independent you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Can you tell me what sort of things you had to remember that now would be written down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh well, yes, you'd have to have your - he - he'd want to know how much stock say of fourteen twenty-four and you'd say twelve dozen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You'd know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Of course you'd know. It was auto - everything was automatic, the whole of your brain. 
You had to have a marvellous brain. And I can remember, I'd only just gone - to be a supervisor this was to do the books, and - a man had - we'd bought a lot of stuff, Parker and Poulson, I can remember the place, a lot of stuff, well I know we had an ord
e
r on this stock, so - I didn't know, I pushed them all in the rack, I never even bothered to look at the invoice or anything you see, pushed them all in the rack. Suddenly they sent for payment. He says to me, you've never checked them in. I haven't had '
e
m. Haven't had 'em. See, nobody'd ever told me anything. I just fell in. So I went to Parker and Pulson, I said, do you know put all your stuff in the racks, I never made note of your invoice. So - and so I explained everything to him, he said, don't worr
y
 my dear. So he gave me another invoice, he said, go and put this in, your all right. So of course - I came back and put them in. I said, oh they've just sent the invoice and of course that was all right. My God, it taught me a lesson. Oh it taught me a l
e
sson. I'd put it all in you see, never - never made a note anywhere, not even to pay the man. But nobody told me, and then we bought a lot of German stuff, and - Mr Baker said to me - here's the invoices, all in German, here's the invoices, so you had to 
g
et - do all that for them. He said - I said, well how shall I book it? So - I said, I've got to book this lot. So he said, you'll find a way out. That happened a lot, let you fall in for it. Well now he could speak a lot of languages, I couldn't speak one
.
 When the man come from the Custom and Excise he said, you've done this wrong. I said, have I? Mr Pine is what his name was. I said - he said, yes. I said, well to be honest I know nothing at all about it, and I can't speak German. I said, I know nothing.
 He said, don't worry, when you close at night I'll come back and he used to come back every night and sit an hour with me to do those things and get them right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Who was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Mr Pine from the - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Customs and Excise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 That's right,
 Customs and Excise man. They came to help me. And then one night he said, how would you like going to a dance. I said, I'd love it. So we went to the Palais. Well as a matter of fact I was at a little dancing class then in Heathcote Street, you know he c
ome and fetched me out, he said, come on, I want you to come - come to the Palais, take me out. He said, I think you're a good sport to sit there and struggle like you do an hour every night. Yes, he did do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 I was going to ask you did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - we didn't - we didn't - dad didn't let us out but mother did. And we - had a kitchen, there was a table and the chairs all round the table, so mother used to pull the table a little bit away from the wall, and the chairs and we'd go
 upstairs and get dressed, dad'd be in the front room, and mother would slip us out the back way, then shut the door you see and push the table back, and that's how we got out dancing. Well - we used to come home at nine o'clock and one night -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How old were you now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - oh I should be - late teens, twenty I suppose, and - one night - we got home at nine o'clock and we told each other what picture we'd seen, of course she got it all off. 'Course when it come to my turn - he didn't believe a wor
d we said. Well then - I can remember my first - oh it was a beautiful dress, ballroom dress, all white done with - royal blue sequin band round me waist and round the sleeves and round the neck 'cos of - yes - oh, when dad saw me, so he - where do you re
c
kon you're going? I said, I'm going to Florrie Danby's twenty-first birthday. So he said, oh? So he said, have a good time, so he didn't know so he said, have a good time. So I go - the first bandmaster I saw was Mr Habditch, I said, don't tell my dad, do
n
't tell my dad I'm here. Anyway I had a lovely evening, and - next day when I got home from dinner dad said, how did you enjoy the dance last night? I says, fine, it was lovely. Oh with me heart in my mouth I said it. He didn't - you see, I was up to him,
 
he didn't say no more. Now if I'd have told him lies he'd perhaps gone for me, but you see I didn't. So I said, oh it was lovely. He said, oh nice twenty-first birthday? I said, yes, it was fine. Oh I said to Mr Hebditch, I says, fancy Mr Hebditch you tel
l
ing my dad. You see, he thought he was being clever. But - it's a wonder he didn't hit me. He nearly did when I had me hair off, because I'd got beautiful hair in those days. And - my - I sat with him for three months at the dinner table when I came home 
from work you see, but I always sat facing him, I took good care never to turn me head.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 He didn't notice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
No. So anyway - this particular day I turned my head for some reason, he saw it. He jumped up, he threw his knife and fork on the table, he
 said, I wouldn't have even minded if I'd have known. So I said, well, what good would it have done you? He says, you're mad the way she's you're your hair, your beautiful hair. I said, yes father, my hair's so beautiful for three months I've sat here and
 
you've never seen it. He walked out. It's funny he - he never came back for me, isn't it funny. If anybody else they daren't speak. But I used to be his match, I - I - did, I saw so much of my other - elder, I thought, you'll not do it to me father. And h
e used to play - when we was kids he played with us on the - on the floor. But he didn't play with me because I used to whip my shoe off and slosh him with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So you were the only one who could cope really were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you went out t
o these dances in the evenings what time did you have to be back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - some - well when there was a proper dance I'd be back for eleven. But - when we used to go to the classes it was nine o'clock, we used to have to be back for nine, I used to hav
e to run all the way home. Well one particular night - I went to - this was a ball, I can remember, oh it was a - I had a beautiful gown on that night and my sister, when I got home, I'd gone with a boy that night, she was hanging out the window, she said
,
 dad's in, dad's in. Oh - I was terrified. So anyway I went in and - he says, where - what time do you reckon this is? I looked at him, I said, it's eleven o'clock. So we sat a long time and - luckily my brother-in-law was in, I don't know why he was so l
a
te but he was in. Thank God he's here, he daren't hit me while he's here, I said to myself. So - we sat a bit longer. He said, what time do you call this? I says, if you go on much longer father it'll be twelve o'clock. So - oh he went on alarming, so I s
ays, well I'm going - aren't you going to get any supper mother, come on, I'm hungry, I wasn't you know but I'd got to say something. So I says, right, well I'm going to bed, goodnight mother. I said, goodnight {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mr Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Harry Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, so - I look at him, up
 and down, got on the stairs, he says, good night me duck. I says, good night. He never liked - he hated dancing. And now my brother, this one, Thomas, he had - a little dance band with Cyril Stapleton. And Cyril Stapleton used to come to our house to pla
y
 the violin, I mean a lot of this that's in the paper's piffle, about Cyril Stapleton, what's in this week, he came to our house and Tom helped him. And Tom got him in - 'cos he worked at Allison and Pikes Tom did and Tom got him into a - a German - maste
r
, music master, who got Cyril Stapleton on. And - we used to go dancing and I went - Tom had a dance band and they had a dance - he had a little dance hall there in Fermin Street and my father went and sat on the balcony, and he - he said he - he'd never 
call it any more because he saw nothing wrong, but then we was too old then I said to bother with it you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What other things did you do in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh we used to go - oh of course later on I don't know, we didn't do anything I don't think, only just sit in the house and knit and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you go to theatres or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh yes, oh yes, we went to the music hall - occasionally, not very often. And the theatres, yes. Used to go and sit in the gods at the theatre, yes, for about threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you were younger you used to go walks did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh yes. Oh yes, we went walks, yes, on a Sunday evening, mother used to take us as far as Trentbridge. And sometimes dad would go. - And - when we were younger dad used to dome and mee
t us out of Sunday school and take us in a landau, we had a lovely ride in the country in a landau with the horses you know. Did I tell you that? Yes. And we kept that up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
When you started work did you make any new friends, girls or boys, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I didn't make many because you see - I don't know, I always seemed to be in charge of people, so therefore I couldn't make friends with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you went dancing who did you go with? People you'd know for years?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - yes, yes. Yes. That's right, friends all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you make any new friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh well, I should make a lot of friends in me time but I can't remember. Can't remember them like personally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And you did bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes. Some 
- not often, but we did bring them home. 'Course mother would always have them but - dad used to like it a bit quite and his own people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, that Mrs Hawkins, she's been my lifelong friend. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Where would you go with Mrs Hawkins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well we used to go dancing. And - we used to go - with a girl at work named Elsie Gow, we used to go to the Albert Hall - to the evening classes there and do needlework or something like that you know, we did that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you go to any other evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No. Can't remember any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes, when we came home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes, we had to tell them everything. Sometimes truth, sometimes not.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your mother expect you home at a certain time or was she more lenient?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh more lenient, yes, we could tell mother everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What time would your father have said you had to be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh nine or ten o'clock. Ten o'clock the latest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So eleven was pretty awful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh very, it was, yes, yes, it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
When did you start going to dancing, it obviously played a big part in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - yes, it did - mother taught - mo
ther was a beautiful dancer, and - she taught us to dance, she used to push all the chairs back and she taught us in our front room. Well then we used to go to - Mrs Halls, that's when we used to have to come home at nine o'clock, we used to go to Mrs Hal
ls, tell our dad we'd gone to the evening home or anywhere, and - Mrs Halls in the Mechanics and that's where we was taught to dance properly you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And that was a good way of meeting the boys too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 That's right, yes, it was, yes, yes. But I alw
ays left them on the ballroom floor, I wouldn't bring them home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You never brought them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No. I'd finish with them on the ballroom floor. It's funny that isn't it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You went to the Palais often did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, I didn't like the Palais
. I didn't like it. I think I've only been there about twice. No, we went to Victoria Halls was open. The old Victoria Halls, you wouldn't remember in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Albert Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. There was a large hall and a small hall, and you - if you went in - I've been in there on my own and stood near the door but I - I've danced every dance all night. You see well you wouldn't do that now would you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did anyone outside the house help your mother look after her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well we used to have a - a washerwoman on a Tuesday th
at was all. And then I used to pay a girl to - to blacklead the grate, give her half a crown a week to blacklead the grate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Was this to get you out of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh yes. Oh yes, so - a girl from work - she used to go on the Saturday and blacklead the grate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When did this happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 On a Saturday morning, she'd go and do it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How old were you to be able to afford half a crown to pay it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh I should - I should be a woman, I should - well I should be in me good job. I wanted to keep me hands clean you see, I had to have me hands nice. Of course we didn't wear rubber gloves then you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well we'd have someone in. We'd have somebody in. Oh yes, have somebody in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Was she often ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No. I was only about six when Tom was born you see, I wouldn't remember.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well not far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Very little. My dad wouldn't let mother go and visit - visit you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Because he was jealous of her - her family, jealous of her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well we never - no, just - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So your mother would have done if she could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh she would, oh yes. Dad had his own friends but they went drinking you see. So they - nobody to bring home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 So he went off drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 On his own, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well never bought them home. We used to have a neighbour come now and again, an old neighbour of mothers that used to come, a Mrs Hollingsworth, she used to come and see mother occasionally, that was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were friends ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Yes, there used to be - there used to be somebody come and she would give them - something, yes. Of course we'd got a big family you see, you couldn't have many in the home could you, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you have any friends in on any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well, at Christmas time or any of our birthdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Would you say that friends invited in were your moth
er's friends or your father's friends or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well it'd be our friends, they - they wouldn't have - the parents wouldn't. Be our friends, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well there - there was - this Mrs Hollingsw
orth, she'd just come down but we didn't - we had very few visitors really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No. No. He'd take her out - oh very rare occasions. Very rare occasions.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 People often tell us in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 That's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did your parents ever get together with their friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No. Just us in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And your father would go with his friends drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did he go to the same place every time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well he belonged a club in town. Sportsman's club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well I think - I think I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Could you tell me what the different ones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - oh I don't know. Well I thought there was three lots of people. I thought there was the poor, the middle class and society. Well we I thought belonged to the middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What sort of people belonged to the middle class like you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What a question, I don't know. What sort of people am I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well who would you put in the middle class before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well I don't know, them that lived well I sho
uld think and lived in nice places. I don't know. Then there was the poor. You know, the poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What sort of people belonged to the poor class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
I don't know what sort of people, but they were poor. Without any shoes - the children never ha
d any shoes on their feet, and the men was always in the pubs drunk. Drinking all the time. There were a lot of drunkenness. Of course I - that part of the world we'd probably see it more, I mean you wouldn't see it here. If they wanted to get drunk they 
drink it in the house wouldn't they here. But used to be in the pubs - they was open all day. The pubs were you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Can you tell me anything about the group you thought of as society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well - they're higher up than us I should imagine, the - the 
rich people, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh no, we wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were you ever told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well we - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Were you taught to show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I can't tell you in which way but we was always told to show - to - respect. I can always remember the boss saying to me - he wanted me to say yes sir to him and I wouldn't, because I thought I was his equal. And - I was in my job, as far a
s he was concerned, and I'd say - I'd say something and say - all right Mr Baker. Sir. All right Mr Baker. Sir. I said, not for me. Not for me. I said, Mr Baker's good enough for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you were an errand girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh yes. Well the head bosses you
 said yes sir, no sir, oh yes, always. Always.
