\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well I expect it would have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You can't think of anyone in particular to tell us about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes. Mr Frenkingham was a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Well he was, his appearance and everything about him, his manner of 
speech and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 And anyone a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Only me. My mother was. My mother was angel. She was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, there was always policeman walking round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well he was grand. We liked them, you felt - sure and confident in them. They was friends, absolutely friends of yours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 You were brought up to think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes. To think they was your friends, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 No, I don't think so. She'd say, I'll tell your dad, that was enough.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How do you think he treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh I thought they was very good. If - if - they deserved
 a - they deserved anything they got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes. Not the last home, the first home was rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
No I think - I - I really couldn't tell you, I think a man called for the rent, but the last home we was in was rent - was our own. Father's own, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
We really wanted to know something about landlords but you would really have been too young wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you remember ever feeling your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Yes, they did. They did early on. Early on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you remember this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well - I wouldn't know much about it but he always looked after us and we had a good table, I can always remember that. But there have been
 times - of course - not through trade, he gambled his money you see. See that was the trouble, he gambled and drank his money, that was the trouble. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Was he ever actually ill so that he couldn't work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Not - only - no. Only at the finish. He
 died at - seventy-three he died of pneumonia. And I hadn't known him ill before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
So you can't actually tell me about people getting help from the Guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh no, I don't know anything about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you know anyone who did you can tell us anything about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Well I can't tell you anything about them but a lot - a lot of people did. I know my mother used to pay fourpence a week for all of us for medical aid. We used to get - 'cos I used to take that for her on a Monday night, w
e used to pay two and eight and a month. And that - looked after all of us you see. They called it medical aid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
You didn't want to tell me on tape about this terrible Christmas you had when you were turned out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Do you feel you could now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
I could tell you but do you think it ought to be on there? Oh - yes, well we'd been at the shop 'til about - eleven or twelve o'clock that night. And - when we got home - dad had had some - a lot to drink and - that was on the - that was Christm
as Eve. Well then the next day - my sister, she brought her husband along, and he wanted to go and see the football match and my sister didn't want to go. So he says, will - will you go with me {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Ada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}? I said, yes, of course I will. So I put me clothes on and
 went, and we went there. And when we got back there was a turkey in the oven and that, and nobody about. And - it - he'd turned us all out because I'd been - just to a football match with my brother. And he said it wasn't right, to think that I would go 
there, he said, never come home to help to cook the dinner. Well I didn't mind going with Alan, so we was all out - all out in the streets, walking about the streets instead of having a Christmas dinner. See, we did all that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 How old were you when he last hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 Hit me? He didn't do it 'cos I hit him back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13860509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 But he would have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1526330 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12348659\charrsid11145034 
Oh yes. One morning - we got up - I heard somebody scream. I think this was Tom's turning point, I heard somebody scream. And I'd got me big j
ob on at work and I said, Tom there's something going - because there was only Tom and I in the; house, I said, Tom, something's going on downstairs. So - he goes down - Tom gets up - jumps out of bed, he must have put his trousers on, I don't know how he
 
did it, he jumped out of bed, went downstairs again, got up again, went down again like a flash, and I couldn't find - a coat, a dressing gown, nothing to put on, so I run downstairs in me nightdress you see and - they'd - dad was underneath the table - a
n
d he was only a boy and not 'cos he's drunk, dad was underneath the table, Tom - his head was out this end and his legs was out the other, and Tom over him with a iron bar. So I said, give me the iron bar Tom. I'm stood there in me nightdress. So Tom give
s
 it me like a lamb. So - get upstairs and get dressed. So I says to this one on the floor, I says, come on let's have you up, I've got the iron bar in me hand, I said, come on, and I just picked him up like a baby. He used to be a man of seventeen stone, 
and I flung him in a chair, I said, sit in there. I said, now you've asked for all you've got. I said, I can't stand this lot, I can't stand it.
